.TH "kset_create_and_add" 9 "kset_create_and_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kset_create_and_add \- Create a struct kset dynamically and add it to sysfs.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct kset *" kset_create_and_add
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "const struct kset_uevent_ops *uevent_ops "  ","
.BI "struct kobject *parent_kobj "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
the name for the kset
.IP "uevent_ops" 12
a struct kset_uevent_ops for the kset
.IP "parent_kobj" 12
the parent kobject of this kset, if any.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates a kset structure dynamically and registers it
with sysfs.  When you are finished with this structure, call
\fBkset_unregister\fP and the structure will be dynamically freed when it
is no longer being used.

If the kset was not able to be created, NULL will be returned.
